rComments: She's adorable! This class was tons of fun and her portion was a lot of fun because you can see how passionate she is about conservation and her corky attitude is a plus. There's a quarter long project to make sure you have a solid group.

She reads everything off the slides and still explains the axis. Low expectations of students which makes the class an easy A but she is still a student, not a great instructor. Take her class if you want a fairly easy A without learning much or being challenged at all.

She's nice and tries to be helpful but half of the questions asked in class she would refer to the TA to help answer and sometimes go unanswered. You are literally memorizing every single minute detail of her lecture slides for the exams. WAY too much work for a 5 unit course although the curve I believe was generous this was not an easy class.
Really fun field trips and Kristen is great to go into the field and collect algae with. Challenging but overall really fun courses.
